n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Dr. Natalie Mayflower Sours Edwards''' (born 1978) is a senior official with the [[United States Department of the Treasury|United States Treasury]] who is employed in the [[Financial Crimes Enforcement Network|Financial Crimes division (FinCEN)]].<ref name=\"CBSNews2018-10-17\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/natalie-edwards-treasury-fincen-employee-charged-with-leaking-financial-records-in-russia-probe/|title=Treasury official charged with leaking records related to Russia probe|date=October 17, 2018|work=[[CBS News]]|last=Rosenkrantz|first=Holly|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Fox2018-10-18>{{cite news|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/treasury-employee-charged-with-leaking-financial-info-of-trump-team|title=Treasury employee charged with leaking financial info on Trump team was arrested with flash drive in hand, prosecutors say|date=October 18, 2018|work=[[Fox News]]|last=Re|first=Gregg|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> She was arrested on October 16, 2018, for allegedly disclosing [[suspicious activity report]]s (SARs) from October 2017 to October 2018 detailing [[Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections|Russia's involvement in the 2016 presidential election]] to a reporter with [[BuzzFeed News]], which published the series \"The Money Trail\".<ref name=\"CBSNews2018-10-17\"/><ref name=BuzzFeedMoneyTrail>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/collection/themoneytrail|title=The Money Trail|date=|work=[[BuzzFeed News]]|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> The SARs included money transfers and information about [[Maria Butina]], [[Rick Gates (political consultant)|Rick Gates]], [[Paul Manafort]], the [[Embassy of Russia in Washington, D.C.|Russian Embassy in the United States]], and a Russian firm, Prevezon Alexander, LLC., involved with [[money laundering]].<ref name=NYT2018-10-17>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/17/business/treasury-leak-manafort.html|title=Treasury Official Charged With Leaking Bank Reports to Journalist|date=October 17, 2018|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|last=Flitter|first=Emily|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Sputnik2018-10-17>{{cite news|url=https://sputniknews.com/world/201810171068975250-us-treasury-butina/|title=US Treasury Adviser Charged With Leaking Info on Detained Russian Citizen Butina|date=October 17, 2018|agency=[[Sputnik (news agency)|Sputnik]]|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/politics/treasury-official-pleads-not-guilty-in-leaking-case|title=Treasury official pleads not guilty in leaking case|author=|date=January 31, 2019|website=WDIV|accessdate=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe government's decision to charge Dr. Edwards is significant as this appears to be the first criminal case based ''solely'' upon an unauthorized disclosure of a SAR.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneylaunderingnews.com/2018/10/fincen-employee-charged-with-unlawful-disclosure-of-sars/|title=FinCEN Employee Charged with Unlawful Disclosure of SARs to Reporter|date=2018-10-24|website=Money Laundering Watch|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref> The criminal complaint against her contains a footnote that \"Edwards told the Interviewing Agents, in sum and substance, that she is a \u201c[[whistleblower]]\u201d and the government acknowledges she filed a whistleblower complaint and reached out to congressional staffers\". The footnote continues on to note that the whistleblower complaint filed was \"unrelated to the SARs disclosures.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/391067147/u-s-v-Natalie-Edwards-Complaint|title=u.s. v. Natalie Edwards Complaint|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2019-03-25}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Edwards, Natalie}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:United States Customs Service personnel]]\n[[Category:People associated with Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women]]\n[[Category:Whistleblowers]]\n\n\n{{US-gov-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Natalie Mayflower Sours Edwards\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image_upright      = \n| image_size         = <!-- DISCOURAGED per WP:IMGSIZE. Use image_upright. -->\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name above -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth based on age as of date |age |year|mm|dd}} -->\n| birth_place        = \n| baptised           = <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   = <!-- {{disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| body_discovered    = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       = <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = [[United States]]\n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = [[United States]]\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Senior official at [[Financial Crimes Enforcement Network|Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)]]\n| ye